Events : the change in the state of an object is known as an Events

Events are fired to notify code of "interesting changes" that may affect code exection


-> Mouse events(click, double click)
->Keyboard events (keypress, keyup, keydown)
->Form Events(submit)
->Print event and many more

to learn more Events : go to the website npm events

Events Handling in JS

Node.event = ()=> {
    //handle here
}

#Event Objects :
it is a special object that has detail about the event.

All the event handler have access to the Event Object's properties and methods

Node.event = (e) => {
    //Handler here
}

e.target, e.type, e.clientX, e.clientY

# Event Listner

node.addEventListner(event, callback)

node.removeEventListener(event, callback)

*Note : the callback reference should be same to remove 